@zhaoziyangretro It's quite different. "2012" is actually satirizing this point, and the story is actually about how the protagonists without tickets finally get on the ship through their own adventures.
In "The Wandering Earth 2", it is directly assumed that voting determines life and death.
It does not discuss or reflect on whether this is reasonable, but directly assumes it, and does not let the audience think about whether this setting is reasonable. I think this is a big difference
